Nigerians will vote for their next president on February 25th. The country is marred by poverty, corruption and violence, made worse by rotten government. But the erosion of democracy has sparked a fight-back from Nigeria’s youth. In this film, The Economist meets the young people pressing for a better, cleaner government. We also interview Peter Obi, a political underdog who hopes to revive the fortunes of Africa’s largest democracy. 